//drrajeevagarwal.co.in/no-fetal-pole-5-6-7-weeks-meaning-causes/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttarget=\"_self\"></a>\n\t\t\t<h2>\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/no-fetal-pole-5-6-7-weeks-meaning-causes/\" target=\"_self\">No Fetal Pole at 5, 6, or 7 Weeks: What Could It Mean?</a>\n\t\t\t</h2>\n\t\t\t<p>\nWhat Is a Fetal Pole in Pregnancy?\nA&nbsp;fetal pole,&nbsp;also</p>\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/no-fetal-pole-5-6-7-weeks-meaning-causes/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttarget=\"_self\">May 24, 2026</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/hemorrhagic-ovarian-cyst-effects-reproductive-health/\" target=\"_self\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"1600\" height=\"720\" src=\"/assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian.webp\" alt=\"Hemorrhagic Ovarian\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"/assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian.webp 1600w, /assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian-300x135.webp 300w, /assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian-1024x461.webp 1024w, /assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian-768x346.webp 768w, /assets/2026/05/Hemorrhagic-Ovarian-1536x691.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" />\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/hemorrhagic-ovarian-cyst-effects-reproductive-health/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttarget=\"_self\"></a>\n\t\t\t<h2>\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/hemorrhagic-ovarian-cyst-effects-reproductive-health/\" target=\"_self\">Hemorrhagic Ovarian Cyst and Its Effects on Reproductive Health</a>\n\t\t\t</h2>\n\t\t\t<p>\nIntroduction\nHearing the word “cyst” during a scan can</p>\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/hemorrhagic-ovarian-cyst-effects-reproductive-health/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttarget=\"_self\">May 22, 2026</a>\n<h1 style=\"font-weight:600;\">Sexual Pain Relief Specialist In Kolkata</h1>\n<h2>Sexual Pain Relief Treatment - Expert Care by Dr. Rajeev Agarwal</h2>\nMany people silently struggle with painful sex or pain during sex. Since the subject is very personal or uncomfortable, many individuals silently wonder whether painful sex is normal or if they should seek medical help. The truth is that painful sexual intercourse is very common and absolutely treatable.\nDr. Rajeev Agarwal is a trusted sexologist in Kolkata who helps individuals and couples understand why pain during sex occurs and how to treat it. He is one of the best infertility specialists in Kolkata.\n<em>(A sexologist is a medical specialist who diagnoses and treats sexual health concerns and intimacy-related problems.)</em>\n<h2>What Is Painful Sex and Pain During Intercourse</h2>\nPainful sex is medically known as dyspareunia. This refers to discomfort or pain that occurs before, during, or after intercourse. This discomfort can feel like a burning, sharp pain, pressure, or deep pelvic pain, depending on the underlying cause. Some individuals may experience pain near the vagina opening or genital area, while others may feel it deeper in the pelvis during penetration.\nThis kind of discomfort does not only affect physical health but also emotional well-being and relationships.\n<h2>Common Causes of Pain During Sex in Women and Men</h2>\nThere are many medical and physical reasons why sexual intercourse can be painful:\n<ol>\n \t<li>Vaginal dryness</li>\n</ol>\nLack of lubrication, hormonal imbalance, menopause, or certain medications can lead to vaginal dryness. This makes intercourse uncomfortable and causes vaginal pain after sex.\n<ol start=\"2\">\n \t<li>Infections</li>\n</ol>\nUrinary tract infections, yeast infections, or pelvic infections can lead to irritation during intimacy.\n<ol start=\"3\">\n \t<li>First-time discomfort</li>\n</ol>\nMany people experience first time sex pain due to anxiety, lack of lubrication, or muscle tension.\n<ol start=\"4\">\n \t<li>Pelvic conditions</li>\n</ol>\nConditions like endometriosis or pelvic inflammatory disease can cause pain during sexual intercourse.\n<ol start=\"5\">\n \t<li>Stress</li>\n</ol>\nStress, relationship concerns, or previous trauma can also contribute to painful sex.\n<h2>Diagnosis and Evaluation for Sexual Pain</h2>\nIf pain during sex occurs very frequently and affects your emotional well-being, it is important to consult an experienced doctor.\nDiagnosis and evaluation for sexual pain will include:\n<ul>\n \t<li>Detailed discussion about symptoms and medical history as a part of <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/preconception\">preconception care</a> and counselling.</li>\n \t<li>Gentle physical examination if required</li>\n \t<li>Hormonal or infection tests</li>\n \t<li>Evaluation of reproductive health.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Why Choose Dr. Rajeev Agarwal for Treatment of Dyspareunia</h2>\nPatients trust Dr. Rajeev Agarwal as one of the leading sexologists in Kolkata and an experienced fertility doctor for all the right reasons. His team also provides reproductive support through <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/fertility-support-services/\">fertility support</a> services, and specialized care for couples who are planning to conceive.\nDr Rajeev Agarwal is well known for;\n<ul>\n \t<li>Advanced treatment for sexual pain disorders</li>\n \t<li>Support for reproductive and hormonal health</li>\n \t<li>Integrated fertility care for couples planning pregnancy.</li>\n \t<li>Dr. Rajeev is the <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/\">best IVF doctor in Kolkata</a> who specializes in fertility and <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/all-services/\">gynecological services</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\n<h3>What causes pain during sexual intercourse?</h3>\nPainful sex can occur due to infections or lack of lubrication, hormonal imbalance, vaginal dryness, pelvic conditions, or even emotional stress.\n<h3>What are the best treatments for pain during intercourse?</h3>\nThe best treatments for pain during intercourse can include improving lubrication for vaginal dryness, treating infections, correcting hormonal balance, and managing pelvic conditions that might be causing discomfort.\nWhen should someone consult a doctor for pain during sex?\nIf you experience frequent pain during sex that causes stress, it is best to get in touch with a qualified sexologist in Kolkata like Dr. Rajeev Agarwal. He can diagnose the underlying issue and suggest treatment accordingly.\n<h3>How can I get relief from pain after sex?</h3>\nRelief from pain after sex will depend on what exactly is irritating your body. Simple steps like using a good lubricant, allowing enough time for arousal, and relaxing the pelvic muscles can reduce discomfort. If pain happens repeatedly, seek medical guidance to heal your body and make intimacy comfortable again.\n<h3>What causes painful sex and how can it be treated?</h3>\nPainful sex can happen when your body is not comfortable during intimacy. Sometimes the tissue may be sensitive, the pelvic muscles may tighten, or the reproductive organs may be affected by an underlying condition. To treat these conditions, a doctor may suggest medications, pelvic health therapy, lubrications, or treatment for a specific medical cause.\n<h5><strong>Popular Blogs </strong></h5>\n<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/understanding-the-role-of-genetics-in-ivf-success/\">Understanding The Role Of Genetics In Ivf Success</a> | <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/battling-blood-sugar-during-pregnancy-gestational-diabetes-risks/\">Battling Blood Sugar During Pregnancy</a> | <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/sleep-and-hormonal-balance-in-women/\">How Sleep Affects Hormonal Balance &amp; Fertility In Women</a> | <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/birth-control-pills-for-pcos-how-long-should-you-stay-on-them/\">Birth Control Pills For Pcos: How Long Should You Stay On Them?</a> | <a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/can-ovarian-stimulation-affect-your-next-period-cycle/\">Can Ovarian Stimulation Affect Your Next Period Cycle?</a>\n<button>Read More</button>"
